\begin_layout Standard
其中 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is the proton momentum and 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{0}$
\end_inset

is the radiation length,
 for which we use the expressions suggested by Tsai [74] .
 For compound materials,
 the radiation length is calculated according to Bragg's rule [61] :
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X_{0}^{-1}=\sum_{i}w_{i}\,X_{0i}^{-1}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $E_{s}$
\end_inset

